The paper deals with name disambiguation and clustering in a patent database, which involves information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) techniques. The use of random forests and DBSCAN algorithms suggests a focus on machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also mentions feature selection and evaluation, which are common topics in machine learning and natural language processing (NLP) research, falling under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
